content.detailedDescription: My girlfriend and i were out observing the taurid meteor shower when a slow chevron shape with 9-10 lights flew overhead.  i say 9-10 because it appeared to be missing a light.  it was not an even chevron.  the right side of the object was longer.  5 lights on the right side, and four on the left.  it slowly flew overhead at a distance over our heads, it appeared to be above 500 feet as we live in the flight path of burbank airport and was roughly the same height straight above our heads.  it was dark however and i cannot be accurate with the height.  it wasn't just silent, it was that eerie silent,  lacking any noise whatsoever.  a high frequency pitch was in my ears for almost an after witnessing the craft, it was weird because tensions rose between my girlfriend and i after witnessing the craft.  we never fight, so this was out of place.  after an hour or so, the pitch subsided and we came in to go to sleep.
content.summary: Flying chevron shape with dim white/yellowish lights

content.detailedDescription:
1. i was playing my nintendo 64 when i received a phone call from our homie to go look outside at this light.
2. i noticed the object at the peak of a tree in front of my house, the lights were so bright even when clouds covered it.
3. i knew it was in fact a ufo by the way it's lights flashed & the way it was hovering up & down in the sky.
4. the object was at the peak of a tree flashing blue, red & green lights. i used some power lines as a scale & common stars i see every night to see if it was really moving. i noticed it started getting dimmer thus the object then disappeared. after 1 minute has passed, it then reappeared higher from the original spot i saw it at. it was sitting still for over 30 minutes just hovering. i got tired so i decided to go inside. that's when i noticed it was moving further away from my vision. i check outside my window & noticed it was gone. 
5. i was shocked to see a ufo again. it has been 6 years since i saw one but this one was like no other. the lights were amazing. i had time to actually record a sighting i knew i'd see again, making my reaction priceless.
6. i didn't lose sight of it, i just walked in my house because i was tired. although i did look out the window & notice it was gone for good.
content.summary: Glowing object hovering up & down disappears then reappears even brighter

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving to work at 7:30 a.M. heading east on sr419/chuluota rd in oviedo florida. i noticed a sparkle in the sky, which caught my eye. it was about the height of my rear view mirror and to the left just a little. my initial thought was it was an airplane. i leaned forward to look out my windshield to see what it was,  when i noticed a round shinny object in the sky. it wasn't there a split second before, it just appeared out of  nowhere.  it had bright lights and was reflecting the sun. just as soon as i laid eyes on it, (2 to 3 seconds) it just disappeared. it just seemed to melt into the sky. i could not believe what i just saw and kept driving while trying to rationalize what it could have been. i called a co- worker to tell him what i just saw, and while we were on the phone, it appeared again this time high up at cloud level and further to the right.
as i approached the  red light at lockwood blvd, i tried to get my phone set to camera to take a picture, but in a split second it just disappeared again.
content.summary: Driving to work, saw a sparkle in the sky , caught my eye.

content.detailedDescription: My brother called me about 8:30 am and said look out towards the moon. the moon was south west of us .My brother lives about a quarter mile from me a little bit south west. we talked on the phone and watched this object for at least 5 mins until it was out of sight. it was no balloon but looked like it had a satellite disc on one side to the right. there was also a round object above that. when you looked at the bottom it appeared to have the shape of a star on it and it was black looking.My brother was able to take three pictures of it and the  one enlarged really shows some detail of the disc and the star like bottom. i also saw what looked like a disc fly towards this thing and then go west.We really want to know what we saw it was no balloon or blimp. we have the goodyear blimp fly around us all the time . this object was also flying over the akron canton airport .The sky was cloudless and a very beautiful clear morning.Two of the pictures look like it is suspended from something but there was no balloon attached to it the one picture enlarged on my computer to 50% shows some great detail any more than 50% it just gets blurred.I hope someone will contact us to let us know what we saw !!I also have a good weather station and the wind was coming from the south blowing east . if this object was a balloon you would think it would follow the wind east ? this object was traveling mostly north and we think it had to be going 200 to 300 miles an hour.It was about half as fast as a jet travels in our area .
content.summary: My brother and i watched the object from two different locations a quarter mile apart and talked on the phone at the same time. we both saw the same thing from our homes back porches.

content.detailedDescription: I was outside taking my garbage to the road and when i looked up i seen a bright star like object, i continued to watch it because i haven't ever seen a star that big. then, it started fading out like a dying light. i continued to walk to the road and it lit up once more. i watched it dim and brighten for about 20 mins before walking back into my house. i looked back one more time to see if it was still there but, it had vanished. i felt real curious about it, why didn't they react to me watching it? why didn't they make themselves known? i never seen it move but all around it was blinking lights that where coming through the cloud cover. i have never seen anything like it but i'm hoping to see more than this in the future.
content.summary: Lights dimming out then brightening

content.detailedDescription: My girlfriend and a close buddy of ours were camping at chaco canyon on the night of friday 10/30/15.  we had spent the last few hours of daylight exploring the ancient ruins there, taking photos of the ancient walls/kivas and observing/photographing the many petroglyphs.  around 7:00p we started a campfire, ate, and sat back in our chairs to stargaze before the moon came up.  to note, there was no alcohol on-site (not even a single beer, we had actually forgotten to grab anything to drink at the last store/gas station, as we were focused on buying firewood and using the restrooms).  we observed satellites, planes, and had an incredible view of the milky way, in addition to seeing several shooting stars.  at approximately 8:00p, i saw what i thought was another shooting star (streaking from the west/north west to the north/north east), and called out, "shooter!" while pointing toward it.  expecting it to disappear before my girlfriend and friend could react/see it (they initially thought the same thing), what i originally thought was a shooting star (calling out "shooter!" like i always do when i see the flash of a shooting star) stopped on a dime and was apparently a round (or spherical) light (green and white, almost as if it was a fried egg with a green yolk and blurred white rim/border, but all of it was illuminated).  it immediately began to slowly descend straight down (from our perspective), then stopped/hovered, disappeared (it may have still been there, but the lights/glow faded into complete blackness), then reappeared a few seconds later in the same spot, held its altitude for a few seconds, and then continued to descend behind a ridge.  we have no idea how far away from (or close to) us it actually was, but size-wise, if the middle belt star in orion's belt was, say, golf ball-sized, then the object that we witnessed (once it stopped...Descended/disappeared/reappeared/descended behindthe ridge) was roughly bowling ball sized, relatively speaking.  it was also completely silent.  the whole encounter, from the time i called out and pointed, thinking it was another shooting star, to the time it ddisappeared behind the ridge was 10-15 seconds.  the three of us looked at each other, shocked, as none of us had ever seen a ufo, or anything even close to this before.  we didn't see it again, or anything else out of the ordinary, during the balance of the evening..
content.flightPath: Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: While camping, i thought i saw a shooting star, but then it stopped (a large green & white light appeared), descended straight down, stopped again, disappeared (light went out) reappeared a few seconds later in the same spot then desecended behind a ridge

content.detailedDescription: On september 28th day of the blood moon i just left from my parents house approximately 9:30.As i drove down the street i noticed a group of people looking up.As i look up i  notice this fire red bell shaped object  moving across the sky.A few seconds later another one just appears going in the same direction. i turned  the corner  then i stopped  got out of my truck took my phone and started to record. buy this time a third one appeared moving in the same direction. a couple of seconds later the third one stops and turns  off the lights.Buy this time the first two are no longer insight.The third one is just hovering you could just make out the craft. it looked like it had square shape windows that were  slightly brighter.Then the fourth one appears. this one was going much slower then the light went out.Thats when i seen what i belive to be an airplane.A very dark plane with no blinking lights  flying much lower.It was very dark that night the plane looked like it was black. when i was recording i also too a couple of pictures when i enlarged them that's when i was sure i just witness my very first ufo sighting!!

content.detailedDescription: My girl friend and i (we are both in our 50's) were walking the dog as we usually do at 7pm like we do every night at this time. what we took notice of was a large area that was glowing above the clouds tword the northern  sky at a 45 degree angle. the area that was glowing was at least a mile wide. at times there was a faint beam that seemed to be rotating around at 30 sec intervals. we both watched it for 5 mins and commented how strange it was. the sighting started at 7:20 and lasted till 7:25 when the whole area above the clouds dimmed and then went out completely. there was no sound at all, and i have never witnessed anything like that in the 15 yrs i have lived here. we drove down the road to see if there was anything that could have caused it, but we found nothing. this is a rural area zoned r10 so the houses are far apart.

content.detailedDescription: I was alone in bed and awake on july 26, 2006 at approximately 2 am.   i was lying on my back looking out my south facing bedroom window admiring the stars towards the end of the bitterroot valley.  the stars were very bright that night as there was no moon or city lights to mask them.  then suddenly, from what i judged to be about 100 yards in the airspace to the south above my dads house, was a large gun metal black triangular object approximately 50 yards wide silently and very slowly moving from the south to the north.  it made absolutely no sound, and had no lights.  the only reason i could see it was that this object was blocking and unblocking the bright starlight as it moved on its slow,  almost hover like path.  it was moving so slow that i had enough time to sit there blink and think, "what in the hell is that," and even look away and pinch my right hand and say "wake up," only to look back and see it slowly moving directly over the house.  there was a clear and definitive moment where this object disappeared over the eave of the roof.   i have never seem anything like it before or after this event.   i did not chase after it longing for another glimpse as it scared the hell out of me!  it completely defied all principles of aerodynamics.
content.summary: Black triangle silent, no lights moving south to north over house

content.detailedDescription:
At 10:10pm est, tuesday, november 3, 2015, i was standing in my driveway looking up to the sky in the nw direction. i was in my driveway looking to the sky to see the aurora borealis that forecast to possibly be seen in ne ohio between 10pm est and 2am est.

now understand something. i do not drink alcohol or take drugs. i am of sound mind and body. i do not partake in wild fantasies. however, i am fascinated with sitting outside at night and gazing at the stars which i do quite frequently. i also spot satellites and meteorites regularly and i obviously know what they look like. i have a great working knowledge of what is in the night sky on a 'nightly' basis.

on this particular tuesday night, i just happened to be looking in the right place at the right time. i was looking to the nw sky. as i was looking up i saw something moving in the night sky. i immediately yelled to my wife and 28 year old son and pointed up to the sky, "what is that?"

they never saw it, but i saw it as clear as crystal. i have excellent night vision and i had been outside for almost ten minutes so my eyes had adjusted fairly well to the dark conditions. (my wife has night blindness.) 

a v-shaped aircraft flying in a straight line, nw to se. there was absolutely no sound. there were no lights, but i could tell that the lights from the ground were reflecting off of the object. it was grey/metallic in color, with several black circles on each 'wing'.

from the time i first spotted it until it disappeared was less than a minute.

for as long as i remember i have taken an occasion to look to the stars. i walk out every night that it is possible to watch the iss fly overhead. i am not given to jumping to conclusions, nor to letting my imagination or emotions get the best of me.

however, all that being said, on the night of november 3, 2015 @ 10:10pm, i saw something flying in the sky directly over my head. after checking into military stealth aircraft possibilities and/or drone possibilites, i have come to one conclusion: what i saw was highly top secret or not of this earth.

i made a drawing of the object right away on my computer.

i hope you can tell me what this is.
content.summary: V shaped aircraft, no lights, no sounds, flying directly overhead.

content.detailedDescription: It is around january 13, 2009. i was going to work on a very overcast day in hazelton, wv. the skies were dark grey. as i approached my exit, i noticed a very strange cloud formation. in the entire dark grey clouded sky, there was another "cloud".  this cloud was light grey to white. perfectly cylindrical in shape except one end was larger than the rest. never have i seen a cloud occur that was a different color and not in a weather related shape as the surrounding area. the grey clouds were rolling in a northwest to southeast fashion. the light grey to white cloud was pointing almost directly south. hanging in the clouds without explanation. perfectly straight. i finishied my drive to work while completely confused at this " cloud". i took a few pictures with a poor camera on a motorola flip phone. i realize that it is a poor quality. in the 15 minutes that i observed this cloud, it never lost its basic shape. it just did not belong. huge. frankly i was too scared to report this earlier. still makes me nervous to look at the pictures today. even if the picture is blurred one can easily understand how strange these are. this was not an opening in the clouds. it was definitely another "cloud" formation in the main cloud based.
content.summary: Cloud cloaked ship

content.detailedDescription: We were on top of a parking garage facing due north trying to see if the northern lights would be visible on the horizon (they wernt). about 10 min after we got there (between 10 and 1030 pm) we (both my girlfriend and i, the only ones there) saw a flying object that made absolutely no noise and didn't have any lights on it whatsoever. we were about 1 mile from pittsburgh international airport, so there were a few planes in various places in the sky, and it was definitely not one of those. compared to those planes, it was relatively low, as if it has just taken off (was moving away from the airport) so one would think if it were a standard plane, there would be noise from the engines or air rushing past it or whatever... but it was completely silent. not only that, but it was completely dark too, there was not a single light on it. the only reason we saw it was because the sky had some light cloud cover, and it almost seemed to reflect some of the grounds light off of it, but it more so had a small cloud of light around it (very very very dim light, but enough to contrast against the night sky). i keep saying plane like because it kind of had that shape, but the most i could make out was a vague triangle. it moved very fast, with the entire sighting listing maybe 3-4 seconds. i first saw it about 40 degrees above the horizon, and a little more nnw than nw. it seemed to fly straight, while going away from us, disappearing into the darkness maybe 60 degrees above horizon at pretty much due ne. being close to the airport, i doubt it was aliens or anything like that, but it was a flying object that we could not identify, which is a ufo right? there is a military base at the airport, but this was nothing like any kind of military plane i've ever seen.
content.summary: Saw silent plane like thing that was very fast and had no lights on

content.detailedDescription: I walked outside and stood there watching the stars for about 10 minutes, as they seemed very bright because there were no clouds. while talking on the phone, once my eyes adjusted, i saw a black (or transparent because it was dark) object moving at a relaxed rate in what seemed like a fixed path. it appeared 50 feet away from me and about 50 feet above me as well. the object became still for 3 seconds once it was above me/once it reached my brightly lit home, and then continued on at the same rate. i was shocked and awed. i felt stuck where i was, riveted. i noticed it was there when i saw what appeared to be a moving constellation. upon further inspection it blocked out other stars as it moved above me. the front or center (it was difficult to tell where the formation exactly started) had a light-colored part that reflected the street lights which are orange. the whole thing moved silently and smoothly. 3 minutes into the sighting it made the sound similar to the sound of something mechanical moving into place, and it eventually dissipated into the sky. or maybe it just moved too far for me to see. the exterior lights looked like stars in a triangular but jointed formation. i counted 4 "stars" on the object.
content.summary: Standing looking at the stars, appeared to look like a moving constellation.

content.detailedDescription:
on november 03, 2015 at approximately 1950 hours, while working in the capacity of a police officer, myself (detective sergeant) and two other officers (both k-9 officers) witnessed several bright green lights in the sky.
	while standing on wilson ave. and snyder on the boarder of campbell and struthers, ohio, witnesses observed 2 triangular shaped objects in the northwest sky.  witness b was the first to notice them and advised the other two witnesses.  all looked to the northwestern sky to see 2 seemingly equilateral triangular-shaped objects with lights at each angle.  the lights appeared to be an unwavering bright lime-green, with one light forward and the other two in the rear.  due to the limited amount of stars in the night sky, witnesses were unable to determine at this time if the objects were solid or not.  the 2 triangular objects were traveling at a very low speed from northeast to southwest.  the two objects were also traveling very close together.  at this time the 2 objects had crossed over the wilson ave. reference point when witnesses observed a single, lime-green in color, orb-like object following the same flight path, but seemingly lower than the other two.  at this time the two triangular shaped objects further crossed the mahoning river reference point, and began to spread out.  the lead tip light stayed slightly ahead while the two rear lights moved up and further apart, causing an almost straight-line appearance.  the lone orb-light object still trailed in the same flight path and slow speed.  
	as the object flew farther away, witnesses retrieved a pair of binoculars to view the objects.  all that could be observed were the lime-green lights, no structure or other characteristics.  the objects were observed in the same almost straight-line pattern until they traveled so far that they could not be viewed with the binoculars.  witnesses attempted to obtain pictures and video with their cell phone cameras, however due to the objects altitude and distance from the witnesses, the lower focal power of the cameras could not pick up the objects.  due to the single object being of the same characteristics of the lights that created the triangular shape then broke apart, all witnesses believe that there were seven object in total.    
all witnesses agreed that they had never seen aerial crafts with these characteristics before.  all three witnesses have extensive law enforcement careers and all three are military veterans with extensive service time.  one witness is a current mufon field investigator.  it is also to be noted that the youngstown-warren regional airport/vienna airbase (1453 youngstown kingsville rd
vienna, oh 4447) is approximately 14 miles north of the sighting.  this region is also a very busy travel route for commercial and military planes arriving and departing at youngstown-warren regional airport/vienna airbase and the pittsburgh international airport.  during the sighting, which lasted approximately 9-10 minutes, there were several commercial airplanes flying in several different directions and altitudes over the immediate area.
content.summary: Several bright green lights in the sky.
